body:
## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: 4.4.0
While copying worksheets from different workbooks (separate Excel files) to a new workbook, a media error occurred. Images were not copied to the new workbook, and there was also a merge cell issue. The merge cell issue has been resolved with a workaround, but ideally, it should be copied when the model is assigned to clone a sheet.

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->


```javascript
const workbook = await Workbook().xlsx.readFile(...);
const srcSheet = workbook.getWorksheet(sheetName);
const newSheet = workbook.addWorksheet(newSheetName);
//Issue: https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/issues/2584
//newSheet.model = srcSheet.model;  // Error: Worksheet name already exists 
let model = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(srcSheet.model));
model.name = `${srcSheet.name} Copied`;
newSheet.model = model;
newSheet.name = `${srcSheet.name} Copied`;

// Merge cells are not parsed in latest version also- Known bug I guess.
const mergesInformation = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(srcSheet.model)).merges;
mergesInformation.forEach((mergeElement) => { newSheet.mergeCells(mergeElement); });

//Throwing an error: the file did not download
// Source Workbook media(images) are not copying to new workbook media folder.
workbook.xlsx.writeBuffer()
  .then(data => {
      // Create a Blob from the workbook data
      const blob = new Blob([data]);

      // Resolve the Promise with the Blob
      save(blob,'mergedExcels.xlsx');
  });
```

## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

```javascript
// Add media to newSheet to avoid image error;
let mediaLength = this.srcSheet.media.length;
newSheet.media.forEach(element => {
    element.index = mediaLength++;
    this.newSheet.media.push(element);
});
```
